						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone near the temple of Kallēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṁghaṇa—A.D. 1230.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Virōdhi,</hi> during the reign of <hi rend="bold">Siṁhaṇadēva, Phālguṇa s11u. Paḍiyā (Pratipadā), Friday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1230 February 15, Friday.</hi> It records the grant of land made by the <hi rend="italic">mahājanas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Hāhari,</hi> (modern Hāvēri) as <hi rend="italic">nettaru-gey</hi> in memory of <hi rend="bold">Sōveya-Nāyaka,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Chauṇḍaya-Nāyaka</hi> who died in a fight at <hi rend="bold">Kabūru.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
